- Combining scraped metadata with manual cleaning revealed that scale introduces not just more data, but more uncertainty about what counts as a consistent unit of analysis.
- Comparing entries across museum APIs made visible how institutional visibility shapes cultural narratives, since certain periods and mediums appear far more frequently depending on the source.

